summary: -Calm Before the Storm- Robb Stark x Fem!Reader
title: -Calm Before the Storm- Robb Stark x Fem!Reader
body:
Being a ward of Caetlyn Stark was very interesting. I didn’t come from a family as well known or highborn as the Starks but they were respected. I was given to the family after my father and two older brothers were killed in the rebellion, my mother forced me to leave and live with the Starks as she couldn’t stand having a daughter in her home whilst her sons were buried beneath the ground.

As much as I resented my mother for giving me away and taking me away from my home growing older I started to understand. Our family was strong, we had a big army according to Eddard Stark and our family had made a significant difference in the rebellion  helping King Robert Baratheon win.

I started to become restless, my guard and I had been riding for days and I was starting to think that I would go crazy from boredom. “We are nearing Winterfell soon Lady *y/n*. I nodded to my guard and gripped my horse’s reigns tighter.

"How long do you believe?” I looked back to the guard, his name was Jaycob Harris, he had been my guard my whole life. He was there when I found out about my father and brothers, he held me as a cried my feelings out, he was to stay with me.

“Not long soon, we should be there before nightfall” I nodded once again and faced forward making sure my horse stayed on track. It was a welcoming sight seeing the walls of Winterfell, the bells started to sound and tears filled my eyes. I guess this it, I wont be able to go back home now.  Jaycob and I slowly entered under the gate and a saw the friendly face of Lord Eddard Stark, his wife Catelyn with a young Arya with a young Sansa beside on his left and his young sons Robb and Jon as well as their other ward Theon on his right.

I was helped off of my horse by Jaycob and curtsied to the lords and ladys, “Lady *Y/n*, Im glad you arrived here safely” Lord Stark spoke, “May I ask where your mother is?” I looked down trying not to show the lords my tears as sadness overwhelms my feelings, he patted my shoulder “Nevermind that, Robb-” The young lords head shot up “-would you show lady *y/n* to her chambers” he nodded and stepped forwards, pointing out his arm for me to take, I looked to Jaycob and he nodded, I moved and took Robb’s arm with him taking me to the castle.

The castle was cold and quiet and I was getting stuck in my head thinking about my brothers, I loved them, they were too young, I am too young. “How was your ride here?” I was pulled out of my thoughts by Robb.

“Oh it was good I guess milord”

“Im sorry for your loss, if there is anything we can get for you just ask”

“Thank you” We stopped outside a door, “I’m guessing this is where ill be staying?” Robb nodded to me “Thank you milord, I think i’ll go to bed now”, I curtsied and turned to enter the room.

“I’ll get your guard to bring you up some food then” Robb turned and left as I shut my door, I guess this was to be my new life, here in a place I hope one day i’ll call home.

summary: [SPOILERS] Sad realization about the Kingslayer
title: [SPOILERS] Sad realization about the Kingslayer
body:
As most of us know, the reason Jaime is reviled as Kingslayer is for what may be the defining moment of his life, saving the people of King’s Landing knowing his honor would forever be besmirched. I want to discuss how events would play out if he had not done it.

There are really two outcomes that could result if Jaime didn’t slay the king. One, someone lives to light the wildfire and kills half a million inhabitants and Jaime. The other option is that Jaime does not kill Aerys and Ned walks in to the throne room with Aerys alive.

If he didn’t kill the king, he’d be labeled a coward who didn’t die defending the king. Ned would hate him for that just as much as he does for him stabbing the king in the back. If he died in the wildfire, he would be remembered as the one man who could have stopped the tragedy and didn’t. All of his good deeds would be overshadowed by his ultimate failure, causing the deaths of 500,000 innocent people.

TL;DR Jaime Lannister is the embodiment of stuck between a rock and a hard place. No matter what he did that day in the Red Keep, he wouldn’t come out of it retaining his honor. It only reinforces my admiration of his character and the difficult choices he’s had to endure.

Please share any thoughts you have :)



Source: https://ift.tt/2PoYs1C

There are really two outcomes that could result if Jaime didn’t slay the king. One, someone lives to light the wildfire and kills half a million inhabitants and Jaime. The other option is that Jaime does not kill Aerys and Ned walks in to the throne room with Aerys alive.

If he didn’t kill the king, he’d be labeled a coward who didn’t die defending the king. Ned would hate him for that just as much as he does for him stabbing the king in the back. If he died in the wildfire, he would be remembered as the one man who could have stopped the tragedy and didn’t. All of his good deeds would be overshadowed by his ultimate failure, causing the deaths of 500,000 innocent people.

TL;DR Jaime Lannister is the embodiment of stuck between a rock and a hard place. No matter what he did that day in the Red Keep, he wouldn’t come out of it retaining his honor. It only reinforces my admiration of his character and the difficult choices he’s had to endure.

Please share any thoughts you have :)

title: [NO SPOILERS] Everyone mocks my theory
body:
That Daenerys will end up with Tyrion. Seriously, I’m tired of being laughed at. I can’t be the first to have this theory.

Here is my reasoning though. GRRM always unites characters with a challenge or outcome antithetical to their character. So Jaime is a selfish jerk that loses his hand and becomes an honorable altruist, Jon is the bastard that is actually the heir to the throne, Daenerys is the weak helpless girl that becomes a conquerer, Sansa is the naive diva that becomes a hardened political operative, etc. You are all pros, you know this.

So, what is Tyrion’s Achilles heel? Women. And in the book how often is Daenerys described as the most beautiful woman in the world? And how much pain does our beloved dwarf suffer because he just wants to be loved? So how strong would the irony be if the most beautiful woman in the world chooses the ugliest imp? It just fits, IMO.



Source: https://ift.tt/2MB7rya
